3
00:00:14,566 --> 00:00:17,068
being as most of you have no idea who I am,

4
00:00:17,108 --> 00:00:18,990
and I'm keeping you from your day drinking.

5
00:00:19,791 --> 00:00:23,695
My name is Jeff Vogel, and I run a company called Spiderweb Software,

6
00:00:23,735 --> 00:00:24,936
which I started in 1994.

7
00:00:26,177 --> 00:00:29,941
We're a little company, two full-time employees now,

8
00:00:29,981 --> 00:00:30,881
it used to be three.

9
00:00:31,727 --> 00:00:36,510
Most people have never, ever heard of us, but we've been around for a very long time.

10
00:01:01,267 --> 00:01:05,089
This is a full list of the full-length games that we have released for money.

11
00:01:05,729 --> 00:01:09,051
The games in italics are full remasters.

12
00:01:09,091 --> 00:01:11,092
We don't half-ass our remasters.

13
00:01:11,132 --> 00:01:13,453
When we remaster it, we redo everything.

14
00:01:13,913 --> 00:01:17,095
The other games are completely all-new full-length titles.

15
00:01:17,115 --> 00:01:18,296
And we write pretty big games.

16
00:01:19,977 --> 00:01:21,298
God knows you don't want to count all that.

17
00:01:21,598 --> 00:01:23,639
But it's over the time we've been in business,

18
00:01:23,679 --> 00:01:26,800
we've released 16 full-length all-new games,

19
00:01:27,021 --> 00:01:29,342
and 7 remas- sorry, 8 remasters.

20
00:01:30,623 --> 00:01:30,983
What do we do?

21
00:01:31,392 --> 00:01:36,534
Well, this is our very first game, Exile Escape from the Pit, which we released in January

22
00:01:36,554 --> 00:01:38,134
of 1995.

23
00:01:38,515 --> 00:01:45,297
And just to be clear, even by the standards of the time, this was a pretty darn cheap

24
00:01:45,357 --> 00:01:46,018
looking game.

25
00:01:47,138 --> 00:01:53,161
It's adorable, it's functional, it's a clearly recognizable Ultima knockoff, but, you know,

26
00:01:53,401 --> 00:01:55,722
it's cheap and scruffy.

27
00:01:57,242 --> 00:01:57,963
In comparison...

28
00:01:58,372 --> 00:02:02,513
About a month and a half ago, we released Avernum 3 Ruined World, which is a remaster

29
00:02:02,713 --> 00:02:07,654
of Avernum 3, which is itself a remaster of Exile 3 Ruined World.

30
00:02:07,954 --> 00:02:12,035
So we've been around long enough that we are doing remasters of remasters.

31
00:02:12,696 --> 00:02:18,857
And if you look at this, I mean, graphically, production values, it's fine.

32
00:02:19,597 --> 00:02:21,438
We're not crapping ourselves up there.

33
00:02:21,498 --> 00:02:22,218
It's reasonable.

34
00:02:23,298 --> 00:02:26,259
No one's going to mistake it for a AAA title or something.

35
00:02:26,299 --> 00:02:27,560
But it's basically...

36
