00:29:28,438 --> 00:29:34,962
This is a key lesson for anyone who runs a small business or deals in a creative way.

581
00:29:36,163 --> 00:29:38,905
It is a human constant that a certain number of people...

582
00:29:39,267 --> 00:29:43,590
Let's say 10% no matter what the demographic,

583
00:29:43,610 --> 00:29:44,870
if you're talking about people who are left-handed,

584
00:29:44,890 --> 00:29:46,952
people with red hair, people who are gamers,

585
00:29:46,992 --> 00:29:48,132
people who wear mismatched socks,

586
00:29:48,372 --> 00:29:49,353
a certain percentage of those people

587
00:29:49,393 --> 00:29:50,614
are always gonna be mean.

588
00:29:50,634 --> 00:29:52,575
A certain percentage of those people

589
00:29:52,595 --> 00:29:53,796
are always gonna be cranks,

590
00:29:53,876 --> 00:29:55,537
and there's nothing you can do about it.

591
00:29:56,097 --> 00:29:58,478
And when you're building your business world

592
00:29:58,598 --> 00:30:00,559
and your mind environment,

593
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:02,120
you have to take that into account.

594
00:30:02,403 --> 00:30:05,905
And you should remember that often the people who are angriest at you are not going to be

595
00:30:06,185 --> 00:30:06,886
completely anonymous.

596
00:30:06,906 --> 00:30:10,768
They're going to be the people who five years ago were your most devout fans.

597
00:30:11,108 --> 00:30:14,871
And then you changed a thing, and it was their favorite thing, and they don't like you anymore.

598
00:30:15,211 --> 00:30:18,733
Just remember, there is always a very thin line between love and hate.

599
00:30:19,594 --> 00:30:24,337
And so if you're going to make it for your 40 years, shelter your brain.

600
00:30:25,117 --> 00:30:29,480
If there is a sort of input that puts me off my feet and slows down my work, I have to

