00:58:58,962 --> 00:59:01,244
I find that if I've been working on one game for about a year

1211
00:59:01,284 --> 00:59:03,446
and a half, I either need to ship it or do a Hemingway.

1212
00:59:04,567 --> 00:59:07,830
I just can't stand looking at it anymore.

1213
00:59:07,850 --> 00:59:09,071
So I get it a year and a half.

1214
00:59:09,131 --> 00:59:09,892
It's a full game.

1215
00:59:09,952 --> 00:59:10,893
It's basically functional.

1216
00:59:10,913 --> 00:59:14,977
I've made it 25% better, fixed, made 25% of what was bad

1217
00:59:14,997 --> 00:59:15,958
in the last one better.

1218
00:59:15,978 --> 00:59:18,400
I kick it out and go on to the next thing.

1219
00:59:18,440 --> 00:59:21,002
I like having a lot of different games, and I think it's fun.

1220
00:59:21,443 --> 00:59:22,564
We only have a few seconds left.

1221
00:59:22,604 --> 00:59:23,865
Two final pieces of advice.

1222
00:59:24,860 --> 00:59:26,382
Don't be proud of not getting enough sleep.

1223
00:59:26,602 --> 00:59:28,705
You need sleep to live.

1224
00:59:29,225 --> 00:59:34,731
And two, get a chair that's good for your back, because when your back goes, my God,

1225
00:59:34,751 --> 00:59:35,412
you're going to miss it.

1226
00:59:36,993 --> 00:59:37,554
Thank you very much.

